---
description: Code generation style rules
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

When generating code:
- prefer production-ready code over tutorial code
- no placeholder comments instead of implementation
- no excessive inline comments
- add comments only where intent is not obvious
- prefer clear names over abbreviations
- avoid one-letter variables except trivial loop indices
- avoid deeply nested conditionals when guard clauses are clearer
- keep functions focused and short when practical
- do not introduce dead abstractions
- do not over-generalize APIs before there is a real need

When editing existing code:
- preserve local style and naming conventions
- avoid broad formatting-only edits
- avoid touching unrelated imports or code paths